.SH "NAME"
dev_open \- prepare an interface for use\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ dev_open('u
.BI "int dev_open(struct\ net_device\ *\ " "dev" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdev\fR
.RS 4
device to open
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Takes a device from down to up state\&. The device\*(Aqs private open function is invoked and then the multicast lists are loaded\&. Finally the device is moved into the up state and a
\fBNETDEV_UP\fR
message is sent to the netdev notifier chain\&.
.PP
Calling this function on an active interface is a nop\&. On a failure a negative errno code is returned\&.
